title: Number of immigrants in Singapore 2005 to 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of immigrants in thousands, containing a total of 5 data points.
Overall Number of immigrants in thousands has increased over the Year.
Number of immigrants in thousands is slightly increasing from 2005 to 2010, roughly constant from 2010 to 2017, and finally slightly decreasing from 2017 to 2019.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2017 and 2019.
The highest Number of immigrants in thousands, of value 2623.0 was reached at Year 2017
Minimum Number of immigrants in thousands about 1711.0 was reached at Year 2005
